Legs (
Figs. 51–54
). Legs rather short, about 1 / 3 length of the idiosoma. Setal formulae of leg segments as follows: coxae 2 - 2 - 1 - 1 ; trochanters 1 - 1-2 - 1 ; femora 4 - 4 - 2 - 1 ; genua 3 - 3 - 1 -0; tibiae 5 - 5 - 3 - 3 ; tarsi 9 ( 1 ω) - 9 ( 1 ω)- 5 - 5 . Dorsal setae distinctly serrated (
Figs. 51–54
). Tarsus I and II with solenidia Iω 30–32 , IIω 25–28 (
Figs. 51–52
). Tarsal claws uncinate and the empodia pad-like.
